## Install `{{ package_manager }}`

{% if package_manager == 'uv' -%}
[`uv`](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) — fast Python package & project manager.

```sh
# Standalone installer (macOS / Linux):
curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh

# Or via pipx / brew / your OS package manager — see
# https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/

uv --version   # verify
```

After install: `uv sync` to materialise the project environment from
`pyproject.toml` + `uv.lock`.
{%- elif package_manager == 'pixi' -%}
[`pixi`](https://pixi.sh) — conda-ecosystem project manager.

```sh
curl -fsSL https://pixi.sh/install.sh | sh
exec $SHELL                # reload shell so $PATH picks up ~/.pixi/bin
pixi --version             # verify
```

After install: `pixi install` to materialise the environment from
`pixi.toml` / `pyproject.toml`.
{%- elif package_manager == 'conda' -%}
[`conda`](https://docs.conda.io/) — install via
[Miniforge](https://github.com/conda-forge/miniforge#install)
(recommended; conda-forge default channel, no Anaconda ToS issues).

```sh
conda --version            # verify
conda env create -f environment.yml
conda activate <env-name>
```

_Fill in: the actual env name once `environment.yml` is finalised._
{%- elif package_manager == 'poetry' -%}
[`poetry`](https://python-poetry.org/) — Python dependency management.

```sh
curl -sSL https://install.python-poetry.org | python3 -
poetry --version           # verify
poetry install
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'pdm' -%}
[`pdm`](https://pdm-project.org/) — modern Python package manager.

```sh
curl -sSL https://pdm-project.org/install-pdm.py | python3 -
pdm --version              # verify
pdm install
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'hatch' -%}
[`hatch`](https://hatch.pypa.io/) — modern Python project manager.

```sh
pipx install hatch         # or: uv tool install hatch
hatch --version            # verify
hatch env create
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'pip' -%}
`pip` ships with Python. Use a virtualenv:

```sh
python3 -m venv .venv
. .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt   # or: pip install -e .
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'pnpm' -%}
[`pnpm`](https://pnpm.io/) — fast, disk-efficient Node package manager.

```sh
# Via corepack (ships with Node ≥16.13):
corepack enable pnpm
pnpm --version             # verify
pnpm install
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'npm' -%}
`npm` ships with Node.js. Install Node via your version manager
(`nvm`, `fnm`, `volta`, `mise`) using the version pinned in this
repo's `.nvmrc` / `.tool-versions` (if present — otherwise pick the
target version and create one).

```sh
node --version && npm --version   # verify
npm install
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'yarn' -%}
[`yarn`](https://yarnpkg.com/):

```sh
corepack enable yarn       # Yarn ≥2 via corepack
yarn --version             # verify
yarn install
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'bun' -%}
[`bun`](https://bun.sh/):

```sh
curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash
bun --version              # verify
bun install
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'cargo' -%}
`cargo` ships with the Rust toolchain via [`rustup`](https://rustup.rs/):

```sh
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh
rustup show                # honours rust-toolchain.toml if present
cargo build
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'go' -%}
Install Go from [go.dev/dl](https://go.dev/dl/) or via your version
manager (the required version is pinned in the `go` directive of `go.mod`).

```sh
go version                 # verify
go mod download
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'gradle' -%}
Use the project's Gradle wrapper (`./gradlew`) — no system-wide Gradle
install needed. You do need a JDK matching `.tool-versions` /
`mise.toml`.

```sh
./gradlew --version        # verify
./gradlew build
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'maven' -%}
Install Maven (`brew install maven`, your OS package manager, or
[maven.apache.org](https://maven.apache.org/install.html)) and a JDK
matching `.tool-versions` / `mise.toml`.

```sh
mvn --version              # verify
mvn verify
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'dotnet' -%}
Install the [.NET SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download) matching
`global.json` (if present).

```sh
dotnet --info              # verify
dotnet restore
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'cmake' -%}
Install CMake via your OS package manager (`brew install cmake`,
`apt install cmake`, etc.) plus a C/C++ toolchain.

```sh
cmake --version            # verify
cmake -B build && cmake --build build
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'meson' -%}
```sh
pipx install meson ninja
meson --version            # verify
meson setup build && meson compile -C build
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'bazel' -%}
Install [Bazelisk](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazelisk) (recommended)
— it honours the version pinned in `.bazelversion`. The official release
binary is called `bazelisk`; create a `bazel` symlink (or use the
commands below verbatim) so commands elsewhere in the docs work.

```sh
# macOS:  brew install bazelisk
# Linux:  https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazelisk/releases
# Optional shim so `bazel` resolves to bazelisk:
#   ln -s "$(command -v bazelisk)" ~/.local/bin/bazel
bazelisk --version         # verify
bazelisk build //...
```
{%- elif package_manager == 'make' -%}
`make` ships pre-installed on most macOS and Linux systems. On Windows,
install GNU Make via [MSYS2](https://www.msys2.org/), Chocolatey
(`choco install make`), Scoop, or run under WSL. Then install whatever
language-specific toolchain the Makefile targets shell out to.

