## Activate the language toolchain

If this repo pins language versions in `.tool-versions` / `mise.toml`
(the recommended single source of truth — neither file is generated
by the template, so add one as part of project setup),
[`mise`](https://mise.jdx.dev/) is the recommended way to honour those
pins:

```sh
# Install mise (one-time, machine-level):
curl -fsSL https://mise.run | sh

# Activate in your shell (add to ~/.bashrc / ~/.zshrc / config.fish):
eval "$(mise activate bash)"   # or: zsh / fish

# Inside the repo:
mise install                   # installs every pinned tool
mise current                   # show resolved versions
```

If you prefer `asdf` or per-language version managers (`pyenv`, `nvm`,
`rustup`, `rbenv`, …), use the same versions listed in `.tool-versions`.

